@node intro "Whaz goin' on in here ?"
This archive contains patterns in 16 colors to use in conjonction of our 16 colors icons BNSMWBicons. Ned, Gino I and decided to split our work in two archives in order to make the archives smaller :
        -       one for the icons, fonts & brushes
        -       one for the patterns & bootpics

Everybody's not going to download a 2Megs archive to use 400Kb of icons.

The window patterns are in ILBM format whereas the Fullscreens are in PiNG format, which explains their relative slowness to load with multiview. That's why their icons' default tool is set to SYS:Utilities/Multiview SCREEN which can load PiNG picture very fast. @{b}SYS:Utilities/Multiview SCREEN@{ub} is included in the archive & is by Magnus Holmgren.
@endnode

@node req "Was I stupid.. or... stupid ?"
@{b}Minimum@{ub}

An Amiga
OS2.x with NICKPREFS or similar (I don't think 1.x users will be able to use this, but who knows...)
A monitor, TV, some visual interface would be useful

@{b}Recomended@{ub} - @{" * " system "SYS:Utilities/Multiview SCREEN Si_un_fou"}

An Amiga with OS3.x
FastIPREFS to handle your patterns smarter (by H.-W.Schober)
FBlit to use FASTRAM instead of CHIPRAM for the patterns (by Stephen Brookes)

Also you'll need PNG datatype or a program to convert the Full Screens back to ILBM.
@endnode

@node hist "History"

